Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
report_instance_cdb(25.10)                          report_instance_cdb(25.10)

Name
       report_instance_cdb  - Allows you to report the cdB associated with all
       the instances or a subset of instances in a design

Syntax
       report_instance_cdb

       [-help]

       [-analysis_type {early | late}]

       [{<instance_list> or <collection>}]

       [-output_file <filename>]

       [-quiet]

       [-view <viewname>]

       Allows you to report the cdB associated with all  the  instances  or  a
       subset of instances in a design.

       Note:  This  command must be issued after report_timing, update_timing,
       or update_glitch commands.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes type and  default  in-
              formation  for eachreport_instance_cdb parameter. For a detailed
              description of the command and all of its  parameters,  use  the
              man command:  man report_insance_cdb

       -analysis_type { early | late }
              Specify the analysis type for the query.

              Default: late

       <instance_list> or <collection>
              Specify  the  instance for which the cdB association is desired.
              By default, the cdB association for all  the  instances  is  re-
              ported.

       -output_file <filename>
              Specify the output filename for the instance report to go to. By
              default, the report output is displayed on the screen.

       -quiet Suppresses warning messages for cells missing in CDB files.

       -view {<viewnames>}
              Specifies  the  view names. By default, values for all the views
              are reported.

Examples
              * The following command reports the cdB instance connection  for
                all   the  instances  in  the  design  and  write  it  to  the
                inst_cdb.rpt file:

                > report_instance_cdb -output_file inst_cdb.rpt

              * The following command reports the cdB instance connection  for
                the u5 instance to the screen:

                > report_instance_cdb u5

                VIEW: default_emulate_view -- ANALYSIS TYPE: late

                u5 : inv_t1 : test1.cdb.txt

              * The  following command reports the cdB instance connection for
                the early analysis type for the u5 and u6 instances

                > report_instance_cdb -analysis_type early {u5 u6}

                VIEW: default_emulate_view -- ANALYSIS TYPE: early

                u5 : inv_t1 : test1.cdb.txt

                u6 : inv_t2 : test2.cdb.txt

